<HEADLINE>
FREE TOURIST MAPS OF TAIWAN BEING DISTRIBUTED
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb.  2  (CNA) 02/02/07  19:25:52 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
One million copies of a tourist map illustrating Taiwan's scenic
spots and the road systems leading to them are being distributed
free at more than a 100 locations throughout Taiwan from Friday.
</P>
<P>
The map, in the form of a folding brochure, has been prepared by
the  Tourism Bureau  of the Ministry  of Transportation  and
Communication.
</P>
<P>
In addition to showing the road systems linking Taiwan's most
famous scenic spots, the map also provides information on the
distance between locations and rest areas on freeways.
</P>
<P>
The maps can be obtained at major airports, railway stations,
information centers at freeway rest areas, passenger service
centers at Taipei's mass rapid transit rail system and
information centers at 13 national scenic areas.
</P>
